06/06/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police have arrested seven Kurds who were allegedly planning bomb attacks in Istanbul. 
They include a senior Kurdistan Workers Party commander. 
According to the police, the suspected terrorists were caught while selecting sites for attack.
In other news, Kurdish fighters ambushed a Turkish Army patrol, killing four soldiers late Saturday or early Sunday. 
One soldier was reported injured. 
(NTV - 06/06/05; AP, Reuters - 06/05/05)
